(2299, 1, '2012-01-13 09:11:37', '2012-01-13 09:11:37', 'The quality of the health system is fully compatible with the Danish in many countries. In some developing countries, the quality however much, and outside major cities is the opportunity for qualified medical care is often poor and transportation time for medical care can be long.\r\n\r\nIn many countries, for example. Sub-Saharan Africa and Southeast Asia, the risk of infection with chronic hepatitis (hepatitis B or C) and HIV / AIDS present at the treatment of disease. The infection can be transmitted by blood transfusions and through syringes, needles and other instruments that are reused.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - illness and treatment abroad:\r\n\r\n* Make no treatment with blood or blood products are not tested or cooked.\r\n* Make no injections with reused equipment. You must ensure that used sterile equipment.\r\n* Try to avoid dental visits.\r\n* Acupuncture treatment can involve a risk of infection.\r\n* Get not done tattoos.\r\n* Do not pierce.\r\n* Please bring disposable needles from home. Sold as travel kit at many pharmacies.\r\n* Read the section on travel insurance.', 'Treatment abroad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1039-revision-7', '', '', '2012-01-13 09:11:37', '2012-01-13 09:11:37', '', 1039, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1039-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
