(2286, 1, '2012-01-12 12:07:13', '2012-01-12 12:07:13', 'Frostbite can develop into a very painful and serious condition that can occur even during a vacation in the tropics. For every 150 meters Mon rises, the temperature decreases by approx. 1 ° C, corresponding to 6 ½ ° C if he ascends 1,000 meters up. If it also blowing, cooling occurs faster. Frostbite occurs when tissue temperature falls below 5 ° C and al skin sensation disappears.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - frostbite:\r\n\r\n* Connect frostbite with warm clothes.\r\n* Heat urgently whole body and especially the almost frozen area of 37-40 ° C hot water. This is very painful and can be given painkillers.\r\n* Do not rub or rub of frostbite because it destroys the tissue further.', 'Frostbite', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1053-revision-3', '', '', '2012-01-12 12:07:13', '2012-01-12 12:07:13', '', 1053, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1053-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
