(2284, 1, '2012-01-12 12:06:10', '2012-01-12 12:06:10', 'Fever can be caused by many things, and should always be compared with other symptoms, to find out what disease it is, and whether to seek medical or not. As a rule of thumb, you should see a doctor urgently if you feel generally weak or are unsure whether the fever can be caused by serious illness. Are you in areas with malaria, you should always consider seeking medical advice for fever.\r\n\r\nSmaller children''s temperature can rise quickly to 39 - 40 ° C even in light infections. Here it is important to observe the child''s general condition. Eating, drinking, peeing and playing child, you can wait and see, but the child will be dull, without appetite, and pale, you should immediately consult a doctor with the child. In those areas of the world where there is risk for malaria, you should always be extra vigilant, and as soon as possible find out whether malaria causes fever (blood test), regardless the child''s general condition.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - Fever:\r\n\r\n* Remember to bring a thermometer.\r\n* Drink plenty, preferably bottled water, sodas and non-alokoholiske drink. Remember that coffee and plain tea will have a slightly diuretic.\r\n* Remove most of clothes, so the body can lose heat.\r\n* Use a fan for cooling.\r\n* Add if necessary cold and wet cloth on the forehead, wrists and chest.\r\n* Consult a physician if the fever rises above 40 ° C.\r\n* Consult a physician if the fever does not decline within 1-2 days.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Fever', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1050-revision-3', '', '', '2012-01-12 12:06:10', '2012-01-12 12:06:10', '', 1050, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1050-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
