(1726, 2, '2012-02-13 13:28:24', '2012-02-13 13:28:24', '<a href="http://travelvaccination.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/stockxpertcom_id34707461_jpg_9b28ffcf95563c66683831b8cbe59ca7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-1181" title="travel advice" src="http://travelvaccination.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/stockxpertcom_id34707461_jpg_9b28ffcf95563c66683831b8cbe59ca7-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="937" height="473" /></a>\r\n\r\nGoing travelling should be equal to a number of good experiences, but the good times may be overshadowed by illness and accidents. Fortunately, the vast majority of illnesses and accidents can be avoided if you just take some precautions.\r\n\r\nThis page tells you about these precautions.\r\n\r\nUnder each topic, there are facts about the disease and some practical advice you should follow before and during your trip.\r\n\r\nWe hope you have a great trip!', 'Travel Advice', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '413-revision-11', '', '', '2012-02-13 13:28:24', '2012-02-13 13:28:24', '', 413, 'http://travelvaccination.co.uk/413-revision-11/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1729, 2, '2012-02-13 13:35:22', '2012-02-13 13:35:22', 'Do you have a known allergy, you should also associated with travel to avoid the things that trigger your allergies.\r\n\r\nAllergies can show themselves in several ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Hay fever with runny or stuffy nose, and eyes that itch and watery.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Urticaria which appears with itching, redness and warmth of the skin, possibly buds one or more locations on the body.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Asthma / breathing difficulties / shortness of breath, which can also be triggered by allergies.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Closure example. of hands, eyes, tongue, face, fingers / toes. Any feeling of tightness in the throat.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTravel advice - allergy:\r\n\r\n* If you have any known allergies, please remember to bring your usual allergy medication.\r\n* Do you suffer from food allergies and eating at a restaurant, ask if there are things you can not tolerate the food. Bring possibly a picture of it with you can not tolerate, it can facilitate the language barrier.\r\n* It may be a good idea, also for others to bring non-prescription drugs such as. antihistamine tablets and antihistamine-containing eye drops.\r\n* Are you allergic form of asthma and you do not know this from earlier, you should seek local physician.\r\n* Raises your lip and tongue, or you feel tightness in the throat, you should seek immediate medical attention.\r\n* Have you previously experienced severe allergic reactions, consult your GP before departure for relief.', 'Allergy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1036-revision-4', '', '', '2012-02-13 13:35:22', '2012-02-13 13:35:22', '', 1036, 'http://travelvaccination.co.uk/1036-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
