(2357, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:16', '2012-08-09 18:04:16', 'All food is a potential source of infection. Be careful when choosing what you eat. This will reduce the risk of tourist diarrhea and more serious infections such as. infectious hepatitis, cholera, typhoid and dysentery.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - food:\r\n\r\n* Always keep a good hand hygiene.\r\n* Avoid putting fingers in their mouths.\r\n* Cook food itself if possible.\r\n* Stick to the safe food and stay away from the unsafe food:\r\n\r\nSAFE FOODS\r\n\r\n* Freshly boiled rice.\r\n* Freshly cooked pasta.\r\n* Scalding hot coffee and tea.\r\n* Bread.\r\n* Although tampering / peeled fruit.\r\n* Freshly boiled / nystegt food.\r\n* Bottled water.\r\n* Drinking from the bottle as you open\r\n\r\nUnsafe food\r\n\r\n* Ice cream and ice cubes.\r\n* Salads.\r\n* Uncooked vegetables.\r\n* Raw fish or raw meat.\r\n* Buffetmad\r\n* Unpasteurized milk products.\r\n* Water from the tap.\r\n* Fruits you have not tampered or garbage.\r\n* Dressing containing raw eggs such. mayonnaise.', 'Food', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1072-revision-4', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:16', '2012-08-09 18:04:16', '', 1072, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1072-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2358, 2, '2012-08-10 14:12:34', '2012-08-10 14:12:34', '&nbsp;\n\nForfrysninger kan udvikle sig til en meget smertefuld og alvorlig tilstand, som kan opstå selv under ferie i troperne. For hver 150 m man stiger op, aftager temperaturen med ca. 1°C, svarende til 6½°C, hvis man stiger 1.000 m op. Hvis det samtidig blæser, sker afkølingen hurtigere. Forfrysninger opstår når vævets temperatur falder til under 5°C og al følelse i huden forsvinder.\n\n<strong>Rejseråd - forfrysninger:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Forbind forfrysningen med varmt tøj.</li>\n	<li>Opvarm hurtigst muligt hele kroppen og især det forfrosne område i 37-40°C varmt vand. Dette er meget smertefuldt, og der kan gives smertestillende tabletter.</li>\n	<li>Du skal ikke gnubbe eller gnide på forfrysningen, da det ødelægger vævet yderligere.</li>\n</ul>', 'Frostbid', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1053-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-10 14:12:34', '2012-08-10 14:12:34', '', 1053, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1053-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2359, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:20', '2012-08-09 18:04:20', 'Frostbite can develop into a very painful and serious condition that can occur even during a vacation in the tropics. For every 150 meters Mon rises, the temperature decreases by approx. 1 ° C, corresponding to 6 ½ ° C if he ascends 1,000 meters up. If it also blowing, cooling occurs faster. Frostbite occurs when tissue temperature falls below 5 ° C and al skin sensation disappears.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - frostbite:\r\n\r\n* Connect frostbite with warm clothes.\r\n* Heat urgently whole body and especially the almost frozen area of 37-40 ° C hot water. This is very painful and can be given painkillers.\r\n* Do not rub or rub of frostbite because it destroys the tissue further.', 'Frostbite', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1053-revision-4', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:20', '2012-08-09 18:04:20', '', 1053, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1053-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2360, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:24', '2012-08-09 18:04:24', 'Anyone can suffer from heartburn. Heartburn is usually due to stomach acid flows up into the esophagus. This causes pain and a burning sensation in the throat when the esophagus has no protective lining against acid. The most common causes of heartburn on travel, is quickly consumed meals, strong spices, for fatty foods or too much alcohol. The type of heartburn usually comes after meals.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - although the treatment of heartburn\r\n\r\n* Take antacid medication, available without prescription in many countries.\r\n* Do you have prescription medication at home, remember to bring it.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - heartburn and danger signals\r\n\r\nWhen heartburn, there are danger signals that should cause you to seek medical help.\r\n\r\n* Pain when you swallow.\r\n* Bloody vomiting.\r\n* Bloody or black stools.\r\n* Breathing difficulties.\r\n* Dizziness or pain that radiates into the neck and shoulder.', 'Heartburn', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1059-revision-5', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:24', '2012-08-09 18:04:24', '', 1059, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1059-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2361, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:29', '2012-08-09 18:04:29', 'A wide range of diseases in the tropics transmitted by mosquitoes. Malaria is transmitted by a mosquito that is most active at night, whereas denque fever, yellow fever and Japanese encephalitis transmitted by mosquitoes are most active during the day.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - insect bites\r\n\r\n* Wear long pants, socks and sweaters with long sleeves.\r\n* Wear like clothes in bright colors. Dark colors attract mosquitoes.\r\n* Use an insect repellent agent on the skin. Sleeping under a mosquito net impregnated against mosquitoes, every night. Sleeping anywhere in rooms with mosquito nets mounted on the windows or in rooms with air conditioning.\r\n* If your bedroom does not have air conditioning or mosquito nets for windows, the room should be sprayed with an insecticide.\r\n* The connectors can insect pin or local anesthetic creams used against itching and pain.\r\n\r\n\r\nTravel advice - mosquito nets\r\n\r\n* Along with the regular use of preventive anti-malarial drugs are mosquito nets around the bed the most effective method for preventing malaria.\r\n* The effect of bed nets increased 2-4 times by impregnation with permetrin or deltametrin.\r\n* Mosquito nets impregnated with permetrin is illegal to import, sell or use in the EU. Environmental Protection Agency is just now processing an application for permission to sell bed nets impregnated with deltametrin.\r\n* Consistent use of mosquito nets around the bed reduces the risk of getting malaria by approx. 50%. An impregnated nets should be re-impregnated at 6 months.\r\n* The mosquito net must be so large that it can be bent in under the mattress or sleeping pad and must hang loose so that you can not inadvertently come into contact with it during the night.\r\n\r\n\r\nTravel advice - insect repellents\r\n\r\n* In Denmark sold products AUTANES and Mosi-guard. These products are considered equivalent to such. Jungle Oil containing DEET and not available in Denmark.\r\n* AUTANES, Mosi-guard and DEET can irritate the skin and can not come in contact with mucous membranes, for example. eyes, nose and mouth. AUTANES should not be used on children under 3 years.\r\n* American Health Care recommends the use of DEET-containing products to children as young as 2 months. So Jungle Oil bought abroad can be used for the little ones.', 'Insect bites', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1065-revision-4', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:29', '2012-08-09 18:04:29', '', 1065, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1065-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2362, 1, '2012-08-10 16:46:13', '2012-08-10 16:46:13', 'Reglerne og dækningsområderne for rejseforsikringer kan variere fra selskab til selskab. Det er vigtigt at være ordentligt dækket, da du ellers vil risikere at blive mødt med overordentlige store betalingskrav for en modtaget behandling i udlandet.\n\nDet gule sygesikringsbevis giver dækning ved sygdom i forbindelse med kortere turistrejser indenfor Europa. Sygesikringskortet dækker ikke hjemtransport.Det er endvidere vigtigt at undersøge dækning for tabte feriedage, aflyste ferier, mistet bagage samt eventuel ulykkesforsikring. Vær opmærksom på, at visse sportsgrene (f.eks. dykning, skisport, klatring, paragliding) kan være undtaget dækning overhovedet.\n\n<strong>Rejseråd - rejseforsikring:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Sørg altid for at have en dækkende rejseforsikring.</li>\n	<li>Undersøg om din rejseudbyder har en specialordning med et forsikringsselskab.</li>\n	<li>Undersøg om dit almindelige forsikringsselskab har en årsrejseforsikring.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Det gule sygesikringsbevis</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Du er dækket af dit gule sygesikringsbevis i udlandet, når du</li>\n	<li>Rejser i mindre end en måned.</li>\n	<li>Er på en ferie- eller studierejse.</li>\n	<li>Rejser inden for EU og EØS samt nogle småstater.</li>\n	<li>Ikke har en kronisk sygdom, fx forhøjet blodtryk.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Dækning af udgifter</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Det gule sygesikringsbevis sikrer, at du får refunderet dine udgifter, svarende til den hjemlige dækning.</li>\n	<li>Du kan dog risikere at skulle betale for lægehjælp og medicin direkte på feriestedet.</li>\n	<li>Husk derfor at få kvitteringer på dine udgifter.</li>\n	<li>Du kan få refunderet dine udgifter ved at henvende dig til SOS International. Du skal altid udfylde en skadeanmeldelsesblanket. Du kan anmelde skaden online på SOS'' hjemmeside.</li>\n	<li>Ved tvivlsspørgsmål i udlandet kan du anvende det telefonnummer, som står på bagsiden af kortet og få vejledning fra den telefoniske vagtservice, som har døgnåbent.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Det blå EU-sygesikringskort</strong>\n\nDu skal have et blåt EU-sygesikringskort ved rejse til et EU/EØS land når du:\n<ul>\n	<li>Skal være væk længere end 30 dage.</li>\n	<li>Skal i praktik eller være au pair.</li>\n	<li>Studere eller følge en faglig uddannelse.</li>\n	<li>Hvis du har en kronisk sygdom.</li>\n	<li>Hvis du skal arbejde for din danske arbejdsgiver i udlandet skal du have en godkendt E101 fra Den Sociale Sikringsstyrelse, for at få det blå EU-sygesikringskort.</li>\n	<li>Det blå EU-sygesikringskort er gratis. Du kan bestille det hos din kommunes borgerservicecenter.</li>\n</ul>', 'Rejseforsikringer og sygesikringskort', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1089-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-10 16:46:13', '2012-08-10 16:46:13', '', 1089, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1089-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2363, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:33', '2012-08-09 18:04:33', 'The rules and coverage areas and travel insurance can vary from company to company. It is important to be properly covered, or you''ll risk being met with extraordinary large claims for payment of a received treatment abroad.\r\n\r\nThe Yellow Card provides coverage for illness in the short tourist trips within Europe. Health insurance card does not cover hjemtransport.Det is also important to examine coverage for lost holidays, canceled vacations, lost baggage and possible accidents. Be aware that certain sports (eg. Diving, skiing, climbing, paragliding) can be excluded coverage at all.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - travel insurance:\r\n\r\n* Always have an adequate travel insurance.\r\n* Check if your travel provider has a special arrangement with an insurance company.\r\n* Check if your regular insurance company has an annual travel insurance.\r\n\r\nThe Yellow Card\r\n\r\n* You are covered by your yellow health card in another country, you\r\n* Travels in less than a month.\r\n* Is on a holiday or study tour.\r\n* Travel within the EU and EEA as well as some small states.\r\n* Not have a chronic illness such as hypertension.\r\n\r\nRecovery of costs\r\n\r\n* The Yellow Card ensures that you receive reimbursement of your expenses, equal to the domestic coverage.\r\n* You may risk having to pay for medical care and medications directly at the resort.\r\n* Remember to get receipts for your expenses.\r\n* You can recover your expenses by contacting the SOS International. You should always file a claim form. You can report damage online at the SOS website.\r\n* If in doubt abroad you can use the phone number printed on the back of the card and get guidance from the telephone-call service, which is open around the clock.\r\n\r\nEU Blue card\r\n\r\nYou must have a European blue card on travel to an EU / EEA country when you:\r\n\r\n* Must be gone longer than 30 days.\r\n* Do an internship or an au pair.\r\n* Study or receive vocational training.\r\n* If you have a chronic illness.\r\n* If you must work your Danish employers abroad, you must have an approved E101 from the Social Security Agency, to get the Blue card.\r\n* The blue EU Health Insurance Card is free. You can order it from your municipality''s citizen service.', 'Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1089-revision-5', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:33', '2012-08-09 18:04:33', '', 1089, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1089-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2364, 1, '2012-08-10 16:46:02', '2012-08-10 16:46:02', 'Ved malaria udvikler den smittede anfald med feber, utilpashed og komplikationer, som i værste tilfælde kan være dødelige. Malaria skyldes en lille parasit, der lever i blodet. Malariaparasitten overføres via myggestik fra malariamyg. Malariamyg er mest aktive om natten.\n\nMalaria er en af de hyppigste årsager til sygdom og død på verdensplan. Det skønnes, at der smittes 300 millioner mennesker om året, heraf dør ca. 1 million (overvejende børn under 5 år smittet i Afrika syd for Sahara).\n\nHvert år er der omkring 100 danskere som smittes med malaria på rejser. Blandt rejsende som behandles for malaria efter hjemkomsten vil der forekomme 0,5-1% dødsfald. De fleste smittes i Afrika.\n\nMalaria findes på alle kontinenter, undtagen Europa. Der er områder hvor risikoen er større end andre. Derfor bygger al information om malariaforebyggelse på individuel rådgivning. Der skal herunder tages hensyn til rejsemål, rejselængde, den rejsendes alder, overfølsomhed og/eller andre sygdomme hos den rejsende.\n\n<strong>Rejseråd - Malaria:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Tag forebyggende malariamedicin, hvis du skal til et område hvor der er reel risiko for malaria. Vær præcis med at tage den forbyggende medicin. Læs og følg altid anvisningerne på pakken.</li>\n	<li>Brug insektafvisende middel</li>\n	<li>Sov under et myggenet som er imprægneret</li>\n	<li>Feber under og op til 3 måneder efter ophold i malariaområder, som ikke kan forklares fyldestgørende på anden måde, skal betragtes som malaria, indtil andet er bevist.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Forekomst af malaria</strong>\n\nVed hjælp af nedenstående link kan du danne dig et indtryk af forekomsten af malaria på dit rejsemål, samt få en anbefaling af eventuelt behov for forebyggende malariamedicin: <a href="http://cdc-malaria.ncsa.uiuc.edu/" target="_blank">http://cdc-malaria.ncsa.uiuc.edu/</a>', 'Malaria', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1075-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-10 16:46:02', '2012-08-10 16:46:02', '', 1075, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1075-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2365, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:38', '2012-08-09 18:04:38', 'For malaria develops the infected seizures with fever, malaise and complications in the worst cases can be fatal. Malaria is caused by a tiny parasite that lives in blood. Malaria parasite transmitted by mosquito bites from malaria. Malaria mosquitoes are most active at night.\r\n\r\nMalaria is one of the major causes of morbidity and mortality worldwide. It is estimated that infects 300 million people per year, die ca. 1 million (mostly children under 5 years were infected in sub-Saharan Africa).\r\n\r\nEach year there are about 100 Danes who are infected with malaria while traveling. Among travelers who are treated for malaria after returning there will be 0.5-1% deaths. Most are infected in Africa.\r\n\r\nMalaria occurs in all continents except Europe. There are areas where the risk is greater than others. Therefore builds all the information about malaria prevention in individual counseling. This should take into account travel, distance traveled, the traveler''s age, sensitization and / or other diseases of the traveler.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - Malaria:\r\n\r\n* Take preventative malaria medication if you need an area where there is a real risk of malaria. Be accurate in taking the preventative medicine. Read and always follow the directions on the package (see section on malaria medication).\r\n* Use insect repellent agent (see section on insect bites).\r\n* Sleep under a mosquito net which is impregnated (see section on insect bites).\r\n* Fever during and up to 3 months stay in malarial areas can not be explained adequately by other means, be considered malaria until proven otherwise.\r\n\r\n\r\nPrevalence of malaria\r\n\r\nUsing the link below you can get an impression of the prevalence of malaria at your destination and get a recommendation of any need for preventive malaria medication\r\nhttp://cdc-malaria.ncsa.uiuc.edu/\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Malaria', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1075-revision-5', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:38', '2012-08-09 18:04:38', '', 1075, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1075-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
