(2367, 1, '2012-08-10 16:46:06', '2012-08-10 16:46:06', 'Forebyggende malariamedicin er sammen med konsekvent brug af myggenet over sengen om natten de vigtigste midler til at forebygge malaria. Der findes ikke noget middel som er fuldt effektivt til forebyggelse af malaria, og intet malariamiddel er frit for bivirkninger. Det er derfor vigtigt at valget af malariamiddel tilpasses efter rejsemål og rejselængde, således at risiko for malaria og risiko for bivirkninger afvejes mod hinanden.\n\n<strong>Bivirkninger og malariamedicin</strong>\n\nAlle lægemidler kan have bivirkninger. Bivirkninger er som regel lette og forbigående.\n<ul>\n	<li>Forebyggende malariamedicin bliver tålt godt af de fleste.</li>\n	<li>Milde bivirkninger mod malariamedicin ses ganske hyppigt.</li>\n	<li>Bivirkninger til malariamedicin tåles fint af de fleste, men uanset hvilken forebyggende medicin som vælges, vil 2-5% (svarende til 1 ud af 30) ophøre med at indtage medicinen på grund af bivirkninger.</li>\n	<li>Alvorlige bivirkninger er meget sjældne.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Piller til forebyggelse af malaria</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Ercoquin (klorokin).</li>\n	<li>Lariam (mefloquin).</li>\n	<li>Vibradox, (doxycyklin).</li>\n	<li>Malarone, (atavaquon + proguanil).</li>\n	<li>Paludrine (proguanil) - kan kun købes i Danmark med særlig tilladelse. Danske Lægers Vaccinations Service (DLVS) har tilladelse til at udskive Paludrine.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Om malariamedicin</strong>\n\nErcoquin anbefales som første valg i Danmark og af WHO ved rejser til malariaområder. Der er imidlertid opstået resistente malariaparasitter en rækker steder i verden og Ercoquin anbefales nu kun til få rejsemål, f.eks. i Mellemamerika.\n\nVibradox, Lariam og Malarone betragtes i Danmark og af WHO som værende ligeværdig medicin til forebyggelse af malaria i områder med Ercoquinresistens.\n\nNedenstående er en kort gennemgang af den forebyggende malariamedicin. Ved bivirkninger er der fokuseret på de mest almindelige. Den kortfattede gennemgang kan ikke erstatte en grundig gennemlæsning af den indlægsseddel, som fås ved køb af medicinen på apoteket. Malariamedicin fås kun på recept.\n\n<strong>Ercoquin (klorokin)</strong>\n\nEffektivt og billigt middel mod malaria. På grund af resistensudvikling hos malariaparasitten kan Ercoquin i dag kun bruges ved rejser til få lande typisk i Mellemamerika. Kan bruges af børn og gravide.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Brug:</span> En gang om ugen, fra en uge før, under og 4 uger efter ophold i malariaområde.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Bivirkninger:</span> Træthed er hyppigste bivirkning. Andre er mavesmerter, kvalme, oppustet mave, hovedpine, svimmelhed, udslæt og kløe. Ved indtagelse af Ercoquin kan der optræde sløret syn som bliver normalt igen 8-16 timer efter indtagelsen. Derfor er det en god ide at tage tabletterne til aftensmaden.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Forsigtighedsregler:</span> Må ikke tages af patienter med psoriasis, klorokin allergi, myastenia gravis, retinopati, epilepsi eller alvorlig hørenedsættelse. Bør ikke tages sammen med digoxin.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Amning:</span> Kan benyttes.\n\n<strong>Malarone (atavaquon + proguanil)</strong>\n\nMalarone kan bruges til forebyggelse af Ercoquinresistent malaria. Malarone er relativt dyrt og koster ca. 25 kroner om dagen. Kan bruges af børn. Må ikke bruges af gravide.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Brug:</span> Tages en gang dagligt, fra en dag før, under og 7 dage efter ophold i malariaområde.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Bivirkninger:</span> Kvalme, opkastning, mavesmerter og diarré.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Forsigtighedsregler:</span> Må ikke tages af patienter med svært nedsat nyrefunktion eller af patienter med allergi mod atavaquon eller proguanil.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Amning:</span> Kan ikke anvendes.\n\n<strong>Vibradox (doxycyklin)</strong>\n\nVibradox kan bruges til forebyggelse af Ercoquinresistent malaria. Vibradox er egentlig et antiobiotika mod bakterier, men har også god virkning mod malaria. Doxycyklin må ikke bruges af børn under 12 år eller gravide.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Brug:</span> Tages en gang dagligt, fra en dag før, under og 4 uger efter ophold i malariaområde.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Bivirkninger:</span> Kvalme. Kan forøge følsomheden for sollys, hvorfor der bør bæres solcreme og udvises forsigtighed ved ophold i solen.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Forsigtighedsregler:</span> Må ikke tages ved allergi mod doxycyklin. Dosis nedsættes ved nyre- eller leversvigt.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Amning:</span> Kan ikke anvendes.\n\n<strong>Lariam (mefloquin)</strong>\n\nLariam kan bruges til forebyggelse af malaria i områder med Ercoquinresistens. På grund af psykiske bivirkninger, herunder mareridt, anbefaler Danske Lægers Vaccinations Service (DLVS) dog kun brug i sjældne tilfælde, f.eks. ved gode erfaringer med brug af Lariam tidligere. Bør ikke bruges af gravide og graviditet skal undgås i 3 måneder efter brug.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Brug:</span> Tages en gang ugentligt senest fra en ugen før, under og 4 uger efter ophold i malariaområde. Bør indtages sammen med føde for at undgå opkastning.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Bivirkninger:</span> Kvalme, opkastning, mavesmerter, diarré, hovedpine, døsighed, svimmelhed og søvnforstyrrelser blandt andet med mareridt. Af ikke almindelige bivirkninger bør andre psykiske bivirkninger nævnes: hallucinationer, psykose, agitation, angst, depression, konfusion og aggressivitet. De psykiske bivirkninger ophører efter brug.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Forsigtighedsregler:</span> Bør ikke benyttes af personer med psykiske lidelser, epilepsi eller nedsat leverfunktion. Må ikke bruges ved mefloquin allergi. På grund af risiko for psykiske bivirkninger tillader nogle dykkercentre ikke brug af Lariam. Første gang Lariam opstartes bør du påbegynde 4 uger før afrejse, idet de fleste psykiske bivirkninger opstår inden 3 uger, således at du eventuelt har tid til at skifte til et andet præparat.\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Amning:</span> Bør ikke anvendes.\n\n<strong>Paludrine (proguanil)</strong>\n\nPaludrine kan i kombination med Ercoquin anvendes i nogle få lande. Paludrine markedsføres ikke i Danmark længere og kan kun fås med særlig tilladelse. Til områder, hvor man før anbefalede Ercoquin og Paludrine i kombination, kan du nu bruge Malarone, Vibradox eller Lariam. Paludrine i kombination med Ercoquin kan bruges til gravide, se afsnit nedenfor.\n\n<strong>Malaria og graviditet</strong>\n\nDanske Lægers Vaccinations Service (DLVS) fraråder alle gravide at rejse til områder med malaria. Malaria i forbindelse med graviditet medfører en øget risiko for såvel mor som barn. Er du gravid, bør du kun rejse til områder med malaria, hvis det er absolut nødvendigt. Både Ercoquin og Paludrine kan anvendes under graviditet. Hvis en gravid indtager Paludrine tabletter, bør hun samtidig indtage en tablet på 5 mg folinsyre dagligt. DLVS har tilladelse til at udskrive Paludrine i særlige tilfælde, herunder til gravide.\n\n<strong>Valg af malariamedicin til dit rejsemål</strong>\n\nVed hjælp af nedenstående link kan du danne dig et indtryk af forekomsten af malaria og hvilken medicin der kan bruges på dit rejsemål: <a href="http://cdc-malaria.ncsa.uiuc.edu/" target="_blank">http://cdc-malaria.ncsa.uiuc.edu/</a>', 'Malariamedicin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1079-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-10 16:46:06', '2012-08-10 16:46:06', '', 1079, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1079-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2368, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:42', '2012-08-09 18:04:42', 'Preventive anti-malarial drugs, along with consistent use of mosquito nets over the bed at night the main means of preventing malaria. There is no way that is fully effective in preventing malaria and no malaria agent is free from side effects. It is therefore important that the choice of malaria means adapted to travel and journey length, so that the risk of malaria and the risk of adverse effects balanced against each other.\r\n\r\nSide effects and anti-malarial drugs\r\n\r\nAll medicines can have side effects. Side effects are usually mild and transient.\r\n\r\n* Preventative Malaria medication is well tolerated by most people.\r\n* Mild side effects from antimalarial drugs is seen quite frequently.\r\n* Side effects of malaria medication is tolerated well by most, but whatever preventive medicine as selected, 2-5% (equivalent to 1 out of 30) stop taking medication because of side effects.\r\n* Serious side effects are very rare.\r\n\r\nPills to prevent malaria\r\n\r\n* Ercoquin (chloroquine).\r\n* Lariam (mefloquine).\r\n* Vibradox (doxycycline).\r\n* Malarone (atavaquon + proguanil).\r\n* Paludrine (proguanil) - can only be bought in Denmark with special permission. Danish Medical Vaccination Service (DLVS) authorized to slicing Paludrine.\r\n\r\nAbout malaria medication\r\n\r\nErcoquin recommended as first choice in Denmark and by the WHO when traveling to malaria areas. There is, however, emerged resistant malaria parasites in several places in the world and Ercoquin recommended now only a few destinations, eg. in Central America.\r\n\r\nVibradox, Lariam and Malarone seen in Denmark and by the WHO as being equivalent medicine to prevent malaria in areas with Ercoquinresistens.\r\n\r\nBelow is a brief review of the preventative malaria medication. When side effects have focused on the most common. The brief review can not replace a thorough reading of the leaflet that comes with the purchase of medicine at the pharmacy. Malaria medicines are only available on prescription.\r\n\r\nErcoquin (chloroquine)\r\n\r\nEffective and affordable cure for malaria. Due to the development of resistance in malaria parasite can Ercoquin currently only used when traveling to a few countries typically in Central America. Can be used by children and pregnant women.\r\nUse: Once a week, from one week before and 4 weeks after exposure to the malaria area.\r\nSide effects: Fatigue is frequent side effect. Others include abdominal pain, nausea, bloated stomach, headaches, dizziness, rash and itching. By taking Ercoquin may occur blurred vision which becomes normal again 8-16 hours after ingestion. Therefore, it is a good idea to take the tablets for dinner.\r\nPrecautions: Do not be taken by patients with psoriasis, chloroquine allergy, myasthenia gravis, retinopathy, epilepsy or severe hearing loss. Should not be taken with digoxin.\r\nBreastfeeding: Can be used.\r\n\r\nMalarone (atavaquon + proguanil)\r\n\r\nMalarone can be used to prevent malaria Ercoquinresistent. Malarone is relatively expensive and costs approx. 25 dollars a day. Can be used by children. Not to be used by pregnant women.\r\nUsage: taken once daily from one day before and 7 days of stay in a malaria area.\r\nSide effects: Nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain and diarrhea.\r\nPrecautions: Do not be taken by patients with severe renal impairment or patients with allergy to atavaquon or proguanil.\r\nBreastfeeding: Can not be used.\r\n\r\nVibradox (doxycycline)\r\n\r\nVibradox can be used to prevent malaria Ercoquinresistent. Vibradox is actually a antiobiotika against bacteria, but also has good activity against malaria. Doxycycline should not be used by children under 12 years old or pregnant.\r\nUsage: taken once daily from one day before and 4 weeks after exposure to the malaria area.\r\nSide effects: Nausea. Can increase sensitivity to sunlight, so there should be worn sunscreen and caution by staying in the sun.\r\nPrecautions: Do not be taken by allergy to doxycycline. Dose reduction of renal or liver failure.\r\nBreastfeeding: Can not be used.\r\n\r\nLariam (mefloquine)\r\n\r\nLariam can be used to prevent malaria in areas with Ercoquinresistens. Because of psychiatric side effects, including nightmares, recommends Danish doctors Vaccination Service (DLVS) only needed in rare cases, for example. by positive experiences with the use of Lariam previously. Should not be used by pregnant and pregnancy should be avoided for 3 months after use.\r\nUse: Do a weekly no later than one week before and 4 weeks after exposure to the malaria area. Should be taken with food to prevent vomiting.\r\nSide effects: Nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, diarrhea, headache, drowsiness, dizziness and sleep disturbances among others nightmares. Of uncommon events, other psychiatric side effects include: hallucinations, psychosis, agitation, anxiety, depression, confusion and aggressiveness. The psychological side effects cease after use.\r\nPrecautions: Should not be used by persons with mental disorders, epilepsy or hepatic impairment. Not for use by mefloquine allergy. Because of the risk of psychiatric side effects allows some dive centers do not use Lariam. First Lariam is started you should start 4 weeks before departure, with most psychiatric side effects occurring within 3 weeks, so that you may have time to switch to another product.\r\nBreastfeeding: Should not be used.\r\n\r\nPaludrine (proguanil)\r\n\r\nPaludrine In combination with Ercoquin used in few countries. Paludrine not marketed in Denmark longer and are available only with special permission. For areas where before recommended Ercoquin and Paludrine in combination, you can now use Malarone, Lariam or Vibradox. Paludrine in combination with Ercoquin can be used for pregnant women, see below.\r\n\r\nMalaria and pregnancy\r\n\r\nDanish Medical Vaccination Service (DLVS) advises all pregnant women to travel to areas with malaria. Malaria in pregnancy carries an increased risk for both mother and child. Are you pregnant, you should only travel to areas with malaria, if absolutely necessary. Both Ercoquin and Paludrine can be used during pregnancy. If a pregnant consume Paludrine tablets, she should also take a tablet of 5 mg folic acid daily. DLVS have permission to print Paludrine in special cases, including for pregnant women.\r\n\r\nSelection of malaria medicine to your destination\r\n\r\nUsing the link below you can get an impression of the prevalence of malaria and what medicine can be used at your destination.\r\nhttp://cdc-malaria.ncsa.uiuc.edu/', 'Malaria medication', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1079-revision-6', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:42', '2012-08-09 18:04:42', '', 1079, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1079-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2369, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:47', '2012-08-09 18:04:47', 'Motion sickness, sea sickness and air sickness are collectively called motion sickness. Typical symptoms include headache, drowsiness, paleness, cold sweats, nausea, vomiting and dry mouth. Transportation sickness can strike anyone but is more common in children than adults and frames together women more than men. Symptoms can continue for several hours after the journey has ended, and it is such. not uncommon for a boat ride to feel the ground under a rock for several hours after we have gone ashore.\r\n\r\nShuttle Sick triggered when our brains, including through the balance board, perceive our body movements conflicting with the information our survey gives us. Motion sickness often triggered when children under a road trip reader, thus prevented from following the surrounding landscape with eyes.\r\n\r\nTravel Advice - preventive against motion sickness\r\n\r\n* Try to look out the window so your eyes and your equilibrium body does not provide conflicting information to your brain\r\n* Do not read, draw or watch movies while you drive, sail or fly.\r\n* Take antihistamines. Be aware that antihistamines are effective against motion sickness is not the same as the antihistamines you accept allerigi. The antihistamines that works on motion sickness seems sedative. The sedative effect can be exploited if you want to sleep during the journey. Anti Histamine is available as tablets and mixture over the counter at pharmacies. Can be used by children as young as 1 year.\r\n* Skopolaminplastre, available on prescription from your doctor. The patch should be applied 5-6 hours before traveling. Suitable for children over 10 years. Scopolamine for many will be more effective in treating motion sickness than antihistamine. Effects may persist for some time after you take the patch off. Scopolamine patches recommended for the elderly because it may have an adverse effect on the heart.', 'Motion sickness', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1101-revision-5', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:47', '2012-08-09 18:04:47', '', 1101, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1101-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2371, 2, '2012-08-09 18:04:55', '2012-08-09 18:04:55', 'Venereal diseases such as HIV, hepatitis B, gonorrhea, chlamydia and syphilis occur worldwide. The incidence is especially high among prostitutes. In some parts of the world, such as sub-Saharan Africa and Southeast Asia, the incidence of the deadly disease HIV and hepatitis B is very high.\r\n\r\nUsing a condom provides good protection against STDs, but the protection is not 100 percent. Although the journey is of longer duration and they fall in love with a new partner, use condoms until you are sure that the new partner is not carrying an STD.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - STDs:\r\n\r\n* Always use a condom.\r\n* Keep yourself to have condoms on the trip and check the expiration date.\r\n* Avoid having sex with prostitutes.', 'Sexually transmitted diseases', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1068-revision-6', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:04:55', '2012-08-09 18:04:55', '', 1068, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1068-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
