(2374, 2, '2012-08-09 18:05:02', '2012-08-09 18:05:02', 'Exposure to sun can cause burns and heatstroke. The nearer the equator you are, the greater the risk. The sun is strongest at midday, and the effect is enhanced by water, snow and sand. Sunbeams may serve even in the shade, and can penetrate the thin, loosely woven or tight clothing.\r\n\r\nSmall children should not be exposed to direct sun, and should never be decidedly sunbathe. Use physical sunscreen, and wearing the smaller children nationwide, thin and loose clothing. Remember a hat.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - sunbathing:\r\n\r\n* Do not stay in direct sun for several hours straight.\r\n* Avoid the strong midday sun.\r\n* Apply sunscreen with a high SPF every 2-4 hours and after swimming.\r\n* As a rule of thumb, you should use at least a handful of sunscreen when you apply yourself. Otherwise, you risk using too little.\r\n* Protect especially the ears, nose, shoulders and lips.\r\n* Use sunglasses with UV protection and fits tightly to the face.\r\n* Protect your head with a hat, cap or similar.\r\n* Stay in sunshade.\r\n* Drink plenty of fluids.', 'Sun', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1095-revision-5', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:05:02', '2012-08-09 18:05:02', '', 1095, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1095-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2375, 2, '2012-08-09 18:05:16', '2012-08-09 18:05:16', 'The quality of the health system is fully compatible with the Danish in many countries. In some developing countries, the quality however much, and outside major cities is the opportunity for qualified medical care is often poor and transportation time for medical care can be long.\r\n\r\nIn many countries, for example. Sub-Saharan Africa and Southeast Asia, the risk of infection with chronic hepatitis (hepatitis B or C) and HIV / AIDS present at the treatment of disease. The infection can be transmitted by blood transfusions and through syringes, needles and other instruments that are reused.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - illness and treatment abroad:\r\n\r\n* Make no treatment with blood or blood products are not tested or cooked.\r\n* Make no injections with reused equipment. You must ensure that used sterile equipment.\r\n* Try to avoid dental visits.\r\n* Acupuncture treatment can involve a risk of infection.\r\n* Get not done tattoos.\r\n* Do not pierce.\r\n* Please bring disposable needles from home. Sold as travel kit at many pharmacies.\r\n* Read the section on travel insurance.', 'Treatment abroad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1039-revision-8', '', '', '2012-08-09 18:05:16', '2012-08-09 18:05:16', '', 1039, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1039-revision-8/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2376, 1, '2012-08-10 16:46:09', '2012-08-10 16:46:09', 'Nedenfor ser du forslag til medicin du kan overveje at medbringe på rejsen. For nærmere råd kan du læse mere under de specifikke afsnit.\n\n<strong>Rejseråd – medicin med på rejsen:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Allergi: Antihistamintabletter og antihistamin tabletter.</li>\n	<li>Diarré: Antibiotika (ciprofloxacin eller azithromycin), stoppende håndkøbsmedicin og breve med pulver til rehydreringsvæske.</li>\n	<li>Halsbrand: Syrenedsættende medicin, der fås både medicin på recept og håndkøbsmedicin.</li>\n	<li>Højdesyge: Diamox.</li>\n	<li>Malaria: Medbring den medicin du er blevet ordineret af lægen. Husk myggebalsam.</li>\n	<li>Smerter: Medbring din almindelige smertestillende håndkøbsmedicin.</li>\n	<li>Transportsyge: Antihistaminer mod transportsyge eller skopolaminplastre.</li>\n</ul>', 'Rejseapotek ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1082-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-10 16:46:09', '2012-08-10 16:46:09', '', 1082, 'http://dlvsdk.konscript.net/1082-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
